As of November 9th 2020, a Foreign National (subject to the provisions of the temporary ban) may enter Indonesian Territory after fulfilling the following requirements:
a. health certificate in English from the health authorities in each country;
b. have been 14 (fourteen) days in a region/country free of the Covid-19 virus;
c. a statement of willingness to enter quarantine for 14 (fourteen) days carried out by the government of the Republic of Indonesia.

